description: Number of partitions of 5n such that cn(1,5) = cn(4,5) <= cn(0,5) = cn(2,5) = cn(3,5).
comments: Alternatively, number of partitions of 5n such that cn(2,5) = cn(3,5) <= cn(0,5) = cn(1,5) = cn(4,5).For a given partition, cn(i,n) means the number of its parts equal to i modulo n.
